Subject: [PATCH] Disable download-ci-llvm to fix 404 error

This patch disables the download-ci-llvm option in the bootstrap configuration
which causes 404 errors when trying to download LLVM tools from Rust's CI server.
The error occurs because either the host triple is not supported or old builds
get deleted after a certain time.

By setting download-ci-llvm = false, the build will use locally built LLVM tools
instead of trying to download them from the CI server.

Fixes: Compilation error due to 404 when downloading LLVM from CI server
---
src/bootstrap/defaults/config.toml | 2 +- 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/bootstrap/defaults/config.toml b/src/bootstrap/defaults/config.toml
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/src/bootstrap/defaults/config.toml
+++ b/src/bootstrap/defaults/config.toml
@@ -123,7 +123,7 @@ changelog-seen = 2
 # downloading LLVM from the CI server.
 #
 # Defaults to false if an LLVM from the ci is not available for your target.
-#download-ci-llvm = false
+download-ci-llvm = false

 # =============================================================================
 # General build configuration
